[35m│[0m systems for weaknesses. An AI-based pentester can autonomously scan          [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m networks, applications, and devices, identifying potential vulnerabilities   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m with a high degree of accuracy. Once identified, the system can prioritize   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m these vulnerabilities based on their severity and exploitability, providing  [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m detailed reports and remediation recommendations.\n\n        The ability of  [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m an autonomous pentester to learn and adapt is crucial. Machine learning      [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m algorithms enable the system to continuously improve its techniques and      [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m strategies by analyzing successful and unsuccessful attempts. This iterative [35m│[0m
